Tilling my own grave to keep me level
Jam another dragon down the hole
Digging to the rhythm and the echo of a solitary siren
one that pushes me along, and leaves me so

Someone feed the monkey
while I dig in search of China
White as dracula
As I approach the bottom
Desperate and ravenous
So weak and powerless
Over you

Pale angel go away
Come again some other day
The devil has my ear today
I'll never hear a word you say
He promised I would find a little
Solace and some peace of mind
Whatever, just as long as I don't feel so
Desperate and ravenous
So weak and powerless
Over you

The sun is beautiful in the morning, but dulls throughout the day. I love the stars and the moon because it can make you feel connected to so many people at once just by looking at them.

 

This story's old but it goes on and on until we dissappear.
Calm me and let me taste the salt you breathed while you were underneath.
I am the one who haunts your dreams of mountains sunk below the sea.
I spoke the words but never gave a thought to what they all could mean.
I know that this is what you want. A funeral keeps both of us apart.
You know that you are not alone.
Need you like water in my lungs.
This is the end.

Someone very close to me died yesterday...I called to wish him happy birthday and someone else answered the phone to tell me. I can't handle this. I guess i need you to connect to the rest of the world.

no real reason to update livejournal.....
 i wish i didn't feel so left out of my own life.


kate

I miss friends...the real ones. The ones who showed up at your house just to talk, you went out with after school until late that night, were happy just hanging out even if you were doing the most unproductive things, being called out of school to go to stupid places with a group of those friends who were entertaining and actually cared about you....or the best friend's house you basically lived at, their parents who had dinner ready for you whenever you decided to show up...doing homework with each other, but not actually caring about school...

Those type of people don't exist here...I guess because they've never been able to make real friends in this place because no one is, and you don't really have the same opportunities. I'm missing out on the best times of my life. Here.

kate

It's 9:47pm....about to enjoy a birthday.
I hate becoming so nostalgic - it's repetitive and occurs constantly. Always. It will never end.

I don't understand what's wrong with me, but I haven't been very social or happy with anything going on...I never am. Never, since my 8th grade year, have I been satisified with any of my situations. The disturbing part is that I can't quit - I talk my way into what I want and where I want to be....when I'm there I hate it and the cycle begins again. I guess due to everything piling up since 8th grade, things are just getting worse for me (mentally/emotionally/whatever) and I'm afraid I'll never be able to commit.....however, when I was home for break I can say, for just about the first time that I can think of, I was actually pretty damn happy. My relationship is almost completely mended with my father, which has had the most impact on me in the past few years. My mother is still out of control, but when she upsets me now I can at least go to my father. Everything back at home seems to be calming down and forming into something I don't think I want to miss - I saw my brother for the first time in a year, my sister is thinking about getting married, my mom is getting married, and my dad finally moved to a new house. I feel like I'm seperating myself by being here, and for once I don't want to be...I want to be involved with their lives. For now, I would like to find a cure for my continuous nostalgia. Please.


Kate

I hate this...if there were a million different ways to express how much I can't stand this situation, I would be all over it.

However, I'm going to drink my problems away this evening until morning.
I'm going to be such a worthless human being while I'm back there...I don't want to talk to anyone.
I don't want to do anything.

I hate the fact that I will give in eventually and pretend to enjoy it.
No one there really cares about you - it's bullshit.

This place is a prison
And these people aren't your friends
Inhaling thrills through $20 bills
And the tumblers are drained and then flooded again

There are guards at the on ramps armed to the teeth
And you may case the grounds from the cascades to puget sound,
But you are not permitted to leave

I know there's a big world out there like the one i saw on the screen
In my living room late last night,
It was almost too bright to see
And i know that it's not a party if it happens every night
Pretending there's glamour and candelabra
When you're drinking by candlelight

What does it take to get a drink in this place
What does it take, how long must i wait

Hi Livejournal.
I'm listening to music from Moulin Rouge.

I get on the horse and she was all sorts of bitchy to me 
"Put your head up, heels down, shoulders back, elbows in, and make your horse bend."
Aaahh, the things a trainer is supposed to say. 
It's great to be back in Kansas sometimes...
We went to the Kansas City symphony on Saturday; it was beautiful with the Choir...
I went to church last night with my grandma...it was cute.
I have so far spent the day with my mother; I hope we go to the horse auction tonight with Cliffton, I miss that cowboy.
Paul is going to dinner with us to this greet place - is that weird or is it just me? Inviting your favorite bartender to go out to dinner? He went back to school I guess - He's majoring in Psychology at KU...too bad I think he's probably almost 30. 
I get to see my brother tomorrow for the first time in a year...It's possible that I will start crying at the airport...and look insane hugging him. Go me. 
My sya application came in the mail - it's not going to be easy. 

Bye.

Finals being tomorrow...I have english then AP Environment; in other words, I'm going to fail life tomorrow. I work so hard for Environmental and just can't get what I NEED. I'm also very confused why the cleaning people are sitting at our kitchen table playing cards or something. 

Ummm...I neglect livejournal sometimes, I'm sorry. We go home..so soon...if I can survive this week. I have to still go take care of my horsey poo. ADAAM HOW I LOVE YOU.

okay so I'm not feeling so great about jeramy writing so much about 'us' on xanga because people who shouldn't, do read it. I'm kind of scared of a lot of drama happening back at home because of it, and I've put myself in a weird situation because I don't know what to do. I was wondering if I should be a little suspicious of the whole ordeal because it has happened really fast...but at the same time I don't want to be and I want to let things happen since that's usually the way to go. I go home in 11 days...I'm counting like a freak.

I also can't decide with the  whole school thing either - do I stay or do I go back to public? My friend Heather left me a comment on xanga and told me to go back...it's stuff like that which makes it difficult. I think I should. Kyle and Tyler were sending me messages on my phone last night - it was pretty cute and made me miss home again. Tyler wanted to know which alcohol I wanted for when I come home, aw..and Kyle told me to basically buy a bunch of xbox games and dvds to watch on his 100 inch projector screen tv thing...he's such a freak sometimes. How does any 19 year old afford to live in a three bedroom apartment, have all new furniture, a dog, and now this tv....? The respectable aspect is that he pays for everything on his own and works for it...sort of. His job is ridiculously easy sometimes I think, but he gets paid really well.

Aside from that rant...I want to be home, eating then walking around the plaza at night with a pretty boy, watching the horse carriages,  waiting for the lights to turn on thanksgiving night, then go back to his own place and sleep, nothing else, until late into the next day when it can start all over again. I get this sappy syndrom all the time...but it will happen this time. I found a ton of pictures of the plaza so here we go, my favorite place to be:

 

and of course, the plaza with all the lights turned on thanksgiving night until January..

Some guy's head basically..

The thing in front of the Nelson Atkins Art Museum by the Plaza...this makes me laugh

a typical spring/summer day on tv in kansas city hahaha..

people do live here.

Southern Kansas City:

in the gheetttooo

kansas city also has an obsession with art and lights

the kc library

Amtrak

wow okay I'm done obsessing.

okay so...the election was stressful.

Going home last weekend was such an amazing  relief.

Hanging out with Kyle and Tyler. Driving to Lawrence to hang out with Jeramy in Templin, then staying at Joe's that night. Driving back home the next morning...eating dinners at J. Alexanders the way  life should be. My mom quitting her job...going to a costume party, being intoxicated and full of nicotine driving to Josh's house...getting high with Josh  then the two of us going to sleep. aw.

I cannot wait until I go back in 15 days, I miss it so much more now and  I hate this place but I feel like there really is no place for me...

Kate

I will update this a lot more later too because right now is just really weird....i'm actually really excited to go to dc for interim! But more importantly, I can't wait until I go home this weekend!!!

I just hope everything works out with Alli and Jess...it makes me upset =(

Well, I just lost an entire entry of me hating the world because computers are stupid -

Basically, I want to go home because of how socially fucked up this entire school. I never really though I would want to go home because of the people - I figured it be because I'm away from home or the work would be too stressful. How can some of these people stand themselves? I don't get it. Unfortunately, society is really just as stupid and stresses you out about being successful. Would it be that bad if I didn't come back? I'm afraid I'd hate myself so much...but at the same time I don't know. What would I miss out on? I'm never going to like anything I do anymore, I'm never satisfied with where I am. I have one year left of high school and I don't even know where I want to go to school for that one last year, let alone college. Why can't I just enjoy my time in high school - why don't I just go back to a normal school.

I don't know what to do.

Kate

I'm working on history. I have to make a political cartoon.
Next friday, in a couple hours, I will be leaving for the airport to go home.
Wow.

Kate

my grandma sends me the strangest emails sometimes - she's like the only one in the family who keeps us together by telling all of us what everyone is doing. Is it sad that she is the one to tell me what my grandpa, mom, brother, and sister are doing? I called my dad for the first time since I moved here last friday. It was strange, but a decent talk I think. We discussed me going home and how he wants to see me blah blah.

I'm not sure about this headmaster's business. It's not all that fantastic aside from the no school thing...but eh. I bought a Prague down coat yesterday off of Overstock because, well, it was really cute and really cheap. I'm beyond excited to get it in the mail - I think I should by Friday.

I talked to Josh for an hour last night on the phone. It started with a text message then he just randomly decided to call me and....I don't know what to say other than it was amazing. We used to have this strange...communication block, but it wasn't there at all last night. We talked and talked...and talked until he had to go to sleep. Unfortunately I feel like it might not go anywhere for a long time due to the current circumstances. I hate it, I want to stay home next year but at the same time I'm starting to like it here again. Why??!!

Kate

 ______________________________________

So...it has been a while, lj.

I'm at boarding school; how fantastic. I'm going home in 11 days though and I'm pretty sure that's all I can think about.  After a little time with Jessica and Corgan, I'm back on here.

I wish I could sleep more, and I'm about to buy some sort of medication that makes you drowsy so I can sort of just...sleep on command. I woke up at 7:30 this morning, but I'm glad because I had to go feed the horses. The thought of it when I wake up sucks, but when I'm down there by myself just with the horses...I don't know, this is probably sounding really strange. All I mean is that there is something about it, like getting away from this insane mini-community, just for that short amount of time.

I called my mom on the way back to my dorm, but her boyfriend/fiance thing answered the phone. It was actually very scary, but he assured me it was because she left her phone in his truck and they were both driving seperate cars to go see their horses. He said he might be out here, to campus, the end of this week or next to meet with Mr. Lewis about the indoor riding arena. I'm not very close with the guy, I mean, I've never really spent much time alone with him...but I think I would like to see him, especially if he would take me out to dinner while he's here. He has this weird infatuation with eating at the nicest of nice places, and making sure you feel like royalty while being there...he just loves making you feel like you're someone special. I like that.

and now my left hand is hurting me, I either have carpal tunnel or arthritis.

I feel like taking a shower now though - so have a ....possibly good day. I hate sundays, they are incredibly depressing.

Kate
